cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on analyzing the public exposure of Facebook profile attributes, which falls under the category of social media and online social networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also involves crawling and analyzing large amounts of data, which could fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The analysis of user behavior and privacy concerns could also fall under the category of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Finally, the paper also involves case studies that could fall under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
